    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So it will avoid these kinds of harmful actions \nor anything that might cause irreversible damage  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 536160,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to your environment or to your code or anything \nlike that. So that concept of irreversibility is  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 540720,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "something that you need to instill in the model \nand be very clear about and think about the edge  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 544800,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "cases. How might the model in misinterpret \nthis concept? How might it not know what it  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 549360,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "means? For example, if you want the model to be \nvery eager and you want it to be very agentic,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 554400,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "well, it might go over the top a little bit. It \nmight misinterpret what you're saying and do more  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 558560,
    "dDurationMs": 3680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "than what you expect. And so, you have to be very \ncrisp and clear about the concepts you're giving  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 562240,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the models. Um, some examples of these reasonable \nheristics that we've learned. One is that while  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 567600,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "we were building research, we noticed that the \nmodel would often do a ton of web searches when  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 571680,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it was unnecessary. For example, it would find the \nactual answer it needed. like maybe you would find  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 576720,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a list of scaleups in the United States and then \nit would keep going even though it already had the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 582080,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "answer and that's because we hadn't told the model \nexplicitly when you find the answer you can stop  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 587200,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you no longer need to keep searching uh similarly \nwe had to give the model sort of budgets to think  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 591920,
    "dDurationMs": 5280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "about for example we told it that for simple \nqueries it should use under five tool calls  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 597200,
    "dDurationMs": 5440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "but for more complex queries it might use up to 10 \nor 15 so these kinds of heruristics that you might  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 602640,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "assume the model already understands you really \nhave to articulate clearly. A good way to think  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 607520,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "about this is that if you're managing maybe a new \nintern who's fresh out of college and has not had  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 612240,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a job before, how would you articulate to them \nhow to get around all the problems they might get  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 617600,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "run into in their first job? And how would you \nbe very crisp and clear with them about how to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 621760,
    "dDurationMs": 3680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "accomplish that? That's often how you should \nthink about giving heristics to your agents,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 625440,
    "dDurationMs": 3680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "which are just general principles that it \nshould follow. They may not be strict rules,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 629120,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "but they're, you know, sort of practices. \nAnother point is that tool selection is key.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 634480,
    "dDurationMs": 5760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So as models get more powerful able to handle more \nand more tools. Sonnet 4 and Opus 4 can handle  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 640240,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you know up to a hundred tools even more than \nthat if you have great prompting. But in order  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 644800,
    "dDurationMs": 3840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to use these tools you have to be clear about \nwhich tools it should use for different tasks.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 648640,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So for example for research we can give the model \naccess to Google Drive. We can give it access to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 652880,
    "dDurationMs": 6720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "MCP tools like Sentry or Data Dog or GitHub. It \ncan search across all these tools, but the model  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 659600,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "doesn't know already which tools are important \nfor which tasks. Especially in your specific  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 664480,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "company context. For example, if your company uses \nSlack a lot, maybe it should default to searching  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 669680,
    "dDurationMs": 6080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Slack for company related information. All these \nquestions about how the model should use tools,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 675760,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you have to give it explicit principles about \nwhen to use which tools and in which contexts. Um,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 681120,
    "dDurationMs": 4000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and this is really important and it's often \nsomething I see where people don't prompt the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 685120,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "agent at all about which tool to use and they \njust give the model some tools with some very  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 689840,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "short descriptions and then they wonder like \nwhy isn't the model using the right tool? Well,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 694240,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it's likely because the model doesn't know what \nit should be doing in that context. Another point  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 698640,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "here is that you can guide the thinking process. \nSo people often sort of turn extended thinking on  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 703600,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and then let their agents run and assume it will \nget out of the box better performance. Actually  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 708160,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that assumption is true. Most of the time you will \nget out of the box better performance, but you can  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 712480,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "squeeze even more performance out of it if you \njust prompt the agent to use its thinking well.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 717280,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So for example, for search, what we do is tell \nthe model to plan out its search process. So in  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 722480,
    "dDurationMs": 5520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "advance, it should decide how complicated is this \nquery? How many tool calls should I use here? What  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 728000,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "sources should I look for? How will I know when \nI'm successful? We tell it to plan out all these  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 732880,
    "dDurationMs": 5520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "exact things in its first thinking block. And then \na new capability that the cloud 4 models have is  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 738400,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the ability to use interled thinking between tool \ncalls. So after getting results from the web, we  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 743760,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "often find that models assume that all web search \nresults are true, right? They don't have any,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 748560,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you know, we we haven't told them explicitly that \nthis isn't the case. And so they might take these  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 752640,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "web results and run with them immediately. So, \none thing we prompted our models to do is to use  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 756880,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "this interleaf thinking to really reflect on the \nquality of the search results and decide if they  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 761920,
    "dDurationMs": 3760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "need to verify them, if they need to get more \ninformation, or if they should add a disclaimer  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 765680,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "about how the results might not be accurate. Um, \nanother point with when prompting agents is that  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 770720,
    "dDurationMs": 6240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "agents are more unpredictable than workflows \nor just, you know, classification type prompts.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 776960,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Most changes will have unintended side effects. \nThis is because agents will operate in a loop  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 782000,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "autonomously. And so for example, if you tell the \nagent, you know, keep searching until you find the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 787840,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "correct answer, you know, find the highest quality \npossible source and always keep searching until  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 792400,
    "dDurationMs": 5440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you find that source. What you might run into is \nthe unintended side effect of the agent just not  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 797840,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "finding any sources. Maybe this perfect source \ndoesn't exist for the for the query. And so it  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 802640,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "will just keep searching until it hits its context \nwindow. And that's actually what we ran into as  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 806800,
    "dDurationMs": 4000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "well. And so you have to tell the agent if you \ndon't find the perfect source, that's okay. You  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 810800,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "can stop after a few tool calls. Um, so just be \naware that your prompts may have unintended side  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 816160,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "effects and you may have to roll those back. \nAnother point is to help the agent manage its  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 821280,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "context window. The Cloud 4 models have a 200k \ntoken context window. Um, this is long enough for  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 826880,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a lot of longrunning tasks, but when you're using \nan agent to do work autonomously, you may hit this  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 831920,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "context window and there are several strategies \nyou can use to sort of extend the effective  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 836080,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "context window. One of them that we use for cloud \ncode is called compaction. And this is just a tool  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 840960,
    "dDurationMs": 7040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that the model has um that will automatically be \ncalled once it hits around 190,000 tokens. So near  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 848000,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the context window. And this will summarize \nor compress everything in the context window  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 852160,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to a really dense but accurate summary that is \nthen passed to a new instance of claude with the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 857280,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "summary. And it continues the process. And we find \nthat this essentially allows you to run infinitely  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 862160,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "with cloud code. You almost never run out of \ncontext. um occasionally it will miss details  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 867040,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "from the previous session but the vast majority of \nthe time this will keep all the important details  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 871680,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and the model will sort of remember what happened \nin the last session. Similarly you can sort of  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 876080,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "write to an external file. So the model can have \naccess to an extra file and these cloud for models  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 881920,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "are especially good at writing memory to a file \nand they can use this file to essentially extend  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 887040,
    "dDurationMs": 5680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "their context window. Another point is that you \ncan use sub aents. Um, we won't talk about this  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 892720,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a lot here, but essentially if you have agents \nthat are always hitting their context windows, you  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 897840,
    "dDurationMs": 5920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "may delegate some of what the agent is doing to \nanother agent. Um, which can sort of, for example,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 903760,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you can have one agent be the lead agent and then \nsub agents do the actual searching process. Then  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 908720,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the sub agents can compress the results to the \nlead agent in a really dense form that doesn't  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 912880,
    "dDurationMs": 5440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "use as many tokens and the lead agent can give the \nfinal report to the user. So we actually use this  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 918320,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "process in our research system and this allows you \nto sort of compress what's going on in the search  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 923680,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and then only use the context window for the lead \nagent for actually writing the report. So this  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 928800,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "kind of multi- aent system can be effective \nfor limiting the context window. Finally,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 933680,
    "dDurationMs": 3920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you can let Claude be Claude. And essentially \nwhat this means is that Claude is great at being  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 937600,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "an agent already. You don't have to do a ton of \nwork at the very beginning. So, I would recommend  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 942240,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "just trying out your system with sort of a bare \nbones prompt and barebones tools and seeing where  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 946880,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it goes wrong and then working from there. Don't \nsort of assume that Claude can't do it ahead of  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 951200,
    "dDurationMs": 6960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "time because cloud often will surprise you with \nhow good it is. Um, I talked already about tool  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 958160,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "design, but essentially the key point here is you \nwant to make sure that your tools are good. Um,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 962400,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "what is a good tool? It will have a simple \naccurate tool name that reflects what it does.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 966880,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "You'll have tested it and make sure that it works \nwell. um it'll have a well-formed description  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 971360,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "so that a human reading this tool like imagine \nyou give a function to another engineer on your  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 976480,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "team would they understand this function and be \nable to use it. You should ask the same question  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 981440,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "about the agent computer interfaces or the tools \nthat you are giving your agent. Make sure that  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 987040,
    "dDurationMs": 5680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "they're usable and clear. Um we also often find \nthat people will give an agent a bunch of tools  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 992720,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that have very similar names or descriptions. \nSo for example, you give it six search tools  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 998080,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and each of the search tools searches a slightly \ndifferent database. This will confuse the model.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1002800,
    "dDurationMs": 6160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So try to keep your tools fairly distinct \num and combine similar tools into just one.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1009840,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So, one quick example here is just that you can \nhave an agent, for example, use these different  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1013920,
    "dDurationMs": 6160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "tools to first search the inventory in a database, \nrun a query. Based on the information it finds, it  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1020080,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "can reflect on the inventory, think about it for \na little bit, then decide to generate an invoice,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1025440,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "generate this invoice, think about what it should \ndo next, and then decide to send an email. And so,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1030320,
    "dDurationMs": 4000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "this loop involves the agent getting information \nfrom the database, which is its external  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1034320,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "environment, using its tools, and then updating \nbased on that information. until it accomplishes  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1039520,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the task. And that's sort of how agents work \nin general. So, let's walk through a demo real  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1044480,
    "dDurationMs": 6080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "quick. I'll switch to my computer. Um, so you can \nsee here that this is our console. The console is  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1050560,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a great tool for sort of simulating your prompts \nand seeing what they would look like in a UI. Um,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1055120,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and I use this while we were iterating on research \nto sort of understand what's really going on and  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1060080,
    "dDurationMs": 3920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "what the agents doing. This is a great way to \nthink like your agents and sort of put yourself  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1064000,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "in their shoes. So, you can see we have a big \nprompt here. Um, it's not sort of super long.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1068960,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "It's around a thousand tokens. It involves the \nresearcher going through a research process. We  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1073520,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "tell it exactly what should what it what it should \nplan ahead of time. We tell it how many tool  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1077760,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "calls it should typically use. We give it some \nguidelines about what facts it should think about,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1082480,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "what makes a high quality source, stuff like \nthat. And then we tell it to use parallel tool  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1086720,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "calls. So, you know, run multiple web searches in \nparallel at the same time rather than running them  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1092080,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "all sequentially. Then we give it this question. \nHow many bananas can fit in a Rivian R1S? This  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1097920,
    "dDurationMs": 3840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "is not a question that the model will be able \nto answer because the Rivian R1S came out very  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1101760,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "recently. It's a car. It doesn't know in advance \nall the specifications and everything. So, it'll  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1106800,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "have to search the web. Let's run it and see what \nhappens. You'll see that at the very beginning,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1111200,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it will think and break down this request. And \nso, it realizes, okay, web search is going to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1115520,
    "dDurationMs": 8080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "be helpful here. I should get cargo capacity. \nI should search. Um, woo. Um, and you see here  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1123600,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it ran two web searches in parallel at the same \ntime. That allowed it to get these results back  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1127920,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "very quickly. And then it's reflecting on the \nresults. So it's realizing, okay, I found the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1132480,
    "dDurationMs": 6080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "banana dimensions. I know that a USDA identifies \nbananas as 7 to 8 in long. I need to run another  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1138560,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "web search. Let me convert these to more standard \nmeasurements. You can see it's using tool calls  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1143200,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "interled with thinking, which is something \nnew that the quad 4 models can do. Finally,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1147440,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it's running some calculations. It's about how \nmany bananas could be packed into the cargo space  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1151920,
    "dDurationMs": 16640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of the truck. And it's running a few more web \nsearches. You can see here that this is a fairly"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1168560,
    "dDurationMs": 3040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "pending"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1171600,
    "dDurationMs": 5920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "approximately 48,000 bananas. I've seen the model \nestimate anything between 30,000 50,000. I think  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1177520,
    "dDurationMs": 8400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the right answer is around 30,000. So this is this \nis roughly correct. Um going back to the slides,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1185920,
    "dDurationMs": 5440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "I think that you know this this sort of approach \nof testing out your prompt, seeing what tools  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1191360,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the model calls, reading its thinking blocks, \nand actually seeing how the model's thinking  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1195760,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "will often make it really obvious. um what the \nissues are and what's going wrong. So you'll  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1201120,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "test it out and you'll just see like okay \nmaybe the model's using too many tools here,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1205520,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "maybe it's using the wrong sources or maybe \nit's just following the wrong guidelines. Um  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1210080,
    "dDurationMs": 7280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "so this is a really helpful way to sort of think \nlike your agents and make them more concrete."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1217360,
    "dDurationMs": 6400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Um switching back to the slides."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1223760,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Okay, so eval evaluations are really important \nfor any system. Um, they're really important  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1229360,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "for systematically measuring whether you're \nmaking progress in your prompt. Very quickly,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1234240,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you'll notice that it's difficult to really make \nprogress on a prompt if you don't have an eval  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1238720,
    "dDurationMs": 3520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that tells you meaningfully whether your prompt is \ngetting better and whether your system is getting  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1242240,
    "dDurationMs": 6400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "better. But eval are much more difficult for \nagents. Um, agents are longunning. They do a bunch  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1248640,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of things. They may not they may not always have \na predictable process. classification is easier to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1254240,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "eval because you can just check did it classify \nthis output correctly but agents are harder. So  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1259440,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a few tips to make this a bit easier. One is that \nthe larger the effect size the smaller the sample  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1264640,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "size you mean you need um and so this is sort of \njust a principle from science in general where  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1269680,
    "dDurationMs": 5520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "if an effect size is very large for example if a \nmedication will cure people immediately you don't  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1275200,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "really need a large sample size of a ton of people \nto know that the model is that that this treatment  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1279920,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "is having an effect. Similarly, when you change a \nprompt, if it's really obvious that the system is  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1284800,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "getting better, you don't need a large eval. I \noften see teams think that they need to set up  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1289280,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a huge eval of like hundreds of test cases and \nmake it completely automated when they're just  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1293680,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "starting out building an agent. This is a failure \nmode and it's an antiattern. You should start out  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1298400,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "with a very small eval and just run it and see \nwhat happens. You can even start out manually. Um,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1304240,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "but the important thing is to just get started. \nI often see teams delaying evals because they  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1309120,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "think that they're so intimidating or that they \nneed such a sort of intense eval to really get  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1313840,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "some signal, but you can get great signal from \na small number of test cases. You just want to  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1318160,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "keep those test cases s consistent and then keep \ntesting them so you know whether the model and  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1322720,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the prompt is getting better. You also want to \nuse realistic tasks. So don't just sort of come  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1327920,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "up with arbitrary prompts or descriptions \nor tasks that don't really have any real  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1332560,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "correlation to what your system will be doing. \nFor example, if you're working on coding tasks,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1336880,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you don't won't want to give the model just \ncompetitive programming problems because this is  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1341120,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "not what real world coding is like. You'll want to \ngive it realistic tasks that really reflect what  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1345840,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "your agent will be doing. Similarly, in finance, \nyou'll want to sort of take tasks that real people  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1350560,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "are trying to solve and just use them to evaluate \nwhether the model can do those. This allows you  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1355680,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to really measure whether the model is getting \nbetter at the tasks that you care about. Another  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1360400,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "point is that LLM is judge is really powerful, \nespecially when you give it a rubric. So agents  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1365440,
    "dDurationMs": 3520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "will have lots of different kinds of outputs. \nFor example, if you're using them for search,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1368960,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "they might have tons of different kinds of search \nreports with different kinds of structure. But LMS  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1373920,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "are great at handling lots of different kinds of \nstructure and text with different characteristics.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1378400,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "And so one thing that we've done, for example, \nis given the model just a clear rubric and then  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1382960,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "ask it to evaluate the output of the agent. \nFor example, for search tasks, we might give  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1387600,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it a rubric that says, check that the model, \nyou know, um, looked at the right sources,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1392320,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "check that it got the correct answer. In this \ncase, we might say, um, check that the model  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1397120,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "guessed that the amount of bananas that can fit \nin a Rivian R1s is between like 10,000 and 50,000.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1402960,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Anything outside that range is not realistic. So, \nyou know, you can use things like that to sort of  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1407840,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "benchmark whether the model is getting the right \nanswers, whether it's following the right process.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1413440,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "At the end of the day though, nothing is a perfect \nreplacement for human evals. You need to test the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1417600,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "system manually. You need to see what it's doing. \nYou need to sort of look at the transcripts, look  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1422000,
    "dDurationMs": 6000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "at what the model is doing, and sort of understand \nyour system if you want to make progress on it.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1428000,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Here are some examples of eval. So one example \nthat I sort of showed uh talked about is answer  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1433360,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "accuracy. And this is where you just use an LLM \nas judge to judge whether the answer is accurate.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1438320,
    "dDurationMs": 4560,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So for example in this case you might say the \nagent needs to use a tool to query the number  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1442880,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of employees and then report the answer and then \nyou know the number of employees at your company.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1446960,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So you can just check that with an LM as judge. \nThe reason you use an LMS as judge here is because  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1451360,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "it's more robust to variations. For example, if \nyou're just checking for the integer 47 in this  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1456720,
    "dDurationMs": 5680,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "case in the output that is not very robust and \nif the model says 47 as text you'll grade it  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1462400,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "incorrectly. So you want to use an LMS as judge \nthere to be robust to those minor variations.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1467200,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Another way you can eval agents is tool use \naccuracy. Agents involve using tools in a  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1471840,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "loop. And so if you know in advance what tools \nthe model should use or how it should use them,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1476480,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you can just evaluate if it used the correct tools \nin the process. For example, in this case, I might  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1481680,
    "dDurationMs": 6000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "evaluate the agent should use web search at least \nfive times to answer this question. And so I could  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1487680,
    "dDurationMs": 5280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "just check in the transcript programmatically did \nthe tool call for web search appear five times or  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1492960,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "not. Similarly, you might check in this case \nfor in response to the question book a flight,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1497600,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the agent should use the search flights tool \nand you can just check that programmatically  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1502000,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and this allows you to make sure that the right \ntools are being used at the right times. Finally,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1506800,
    "dDurationMs": 5280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a really good eval for agents is tobench. You \ncan sort of look this up. Towen is a sort of open  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1512080,
    "dDurationMs": 5520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "source benchmark that shows that you can evaluate \nwhether agents reach the correct final state.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1517600,
    "dDurationMs": 5600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So a lot of agents are sort of modifying a \ndatabase or interacting with a user in a way  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1523200,
    "dDurationMs": 5200,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "where you can say the model should always get to \nthis state at the end of the process. For example,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1528400,
    "dDurationMs": 6880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "if your agent is a customer service agent for \nairlines and the user asks to change their flight  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1535280,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "at the end of the agentic process in response to \nthat prompt, it should have changed the flight in  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1540000,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the database. And so you can just check at the end \nof the agentic process, was the flight changed?  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1545120,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "was this row in the database changed to a \ndifferent date and that can verify that the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1549520,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "agent is working correctly. This is really robust \nand you can use it a lot in a lot of different use  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1553920,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "cases. For example, you can check that your \ndatabase is updated correctly. You can check  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1558640,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that certain files were modified, things like \nthat as a way to evaluate the final state that  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1563360,
    "dDurationMs": 9080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the agent reaches. And that's it from us. Um, \nwe're happy to take your questions. [Applause]"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1577440,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Can you talk about building prompts for agents? \nAre you giving it kind of long longer prompts  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1581920,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "first and then iterating or you starting kind \nof chunk by chunk? Uh what's that look like?  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1586080,
    "dDurationMs": 6160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "And can you show sort of a little bit more on that \nthought process? That's a great question. Um can  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1592240,
    "dDurationMs": 5280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "I switch back to my screen actually? I just want \nto sort of show the demo. Thank you. Um, yeah. So,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1597520,
    "dDurationMs": 4000,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you can see this is sort of a final prompt \nthat we've arrived at, but this is not where  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1601520,
    "dDurationMs": 13600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "we started. I think the answer to your question \nis that you start with a short simple prompt."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1615120,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Um, and I might just say search the web \naentically. I'll change this to a different  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1620160,
    "dDurationMs": 6880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "question. Um, how good are the Cloud 4 models \nand then we'll just run that. And so you'll  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1627040,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "want to start with something very simple and just \nsee how it works. You'll often find that Claude  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1631280,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "can do the task well out of the box. But if you \nhave more needs and you need it to operate really  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1636000,
    "dDurationMs": 5120,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "consistently in production, you'll notice edge \ncases or small flaws as you test with more use  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1641120,
    "dDurationMs": 4800,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "cases. And so you'll sort of add those into the \nprompt. So I would say building an agent prompt  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1645920,
    "dDurationMs": 6480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "what it looks like concretely is start simple, \ntest it out, see what happens, iterate from there,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1652400,
    "dDurationMs": 5360,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "start collecting test cases where the model fails \nor succeeds and then over time try to increase the  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1657760,
    "dDurationMs": 4400,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "number of test cases that pass. Um, and the way \nto do this is by sort of adding instructions,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1662160,
    "dDurationMs": 4160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "adding examples to the prompt. But you really \nonly do that when you find out what the edge  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1666320,
    "dDurationMs": 6320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "cases are. And you can see that it thinks that \nthe models are indeed good. So that's great.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1673840,
    "dDurationMs": 4320,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "when I do like normal prompting and it's not \nagentic, uh I'll often give like a few shot  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1678160,
    "dDurationMs": 3280,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "example of like, hey, here's like input, \nhere's output. This works really well for  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1681440,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "like classification tasks, stuff like that, right? \nUh is there a parallel here in this like agentic  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1686320,
    "dDurationMs": 4480,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "world? Are you finding that that's ever helpful \nor should I not think about it that way? That is  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1690800,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "a great question. Yeah. So should you include \nfewshot examples in your prompt and sort of  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1696640,
    "dDurationMs": 3600,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "traditional prompting techniques involve like \ngiving the saying the model should use a chain  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1700240,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "of thought and then giving a few shot examples \nlike a bunch of examples to imitate. We find  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1704960,
    "dDurationMs": 5040,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "that these techniques are not as effective for \nstate-of-the-art frontier models and for agents.  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1710000,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Um the main reason for this is that if you give \nthe model a bunch of examples of exactly what  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1714240,
    "dDurationMs": 4080,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "process it should follow, that just limits the \nmodel too much. These models are smarter than  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1718320,
    "dDurationMs": 4720,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you can predict and so you don't want to tell \nthem exactly what they need to do. Similarly,  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1723040,
    "dDurationMs": 3920,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "chain of thought has just been trained into the \nmodels at this point. The models know to think  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1726960,
    "dDurationMs": 5840,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "in advance. They don't need to be told like use \nchain of thought. But what we can do here is one  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1732800,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "you can tell the model how to use its thinking. \nSo you know I talked about earlier rather than  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1737040,
    "dDurationMs": 3520,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "telling the model you need to use a chain of \nthought. It already knows that. You can just  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1740560,
    "dDurationMs": 4880,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "say use your thinking process to plan out your \nsearch or to plan out what you're going to do  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1745440,
    "dDurationMs": 4960,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "in terms of coding. Reme or you can tell it to \nremember specific things in its thinking process  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1750400,
    "dDurationMs": 4640,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and that sort of helps the agent stay on track. \nAs far as examples go, um you'll want to give  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1755040,
    "dDurationMs": 4240,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "the model examples but not too prescriptive. \nI think we are out of time, but you can come  "
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1759280,
    "dDurationMs": 6160,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "up to me personally and I'll talk to you all \nafter. Thanks. Thank you. Thanks for coming."
    } ]
  } ]
}
